# 
Emma Vauloup

Emma Vauloup is a digital illustrator from France. She's inspired by what comes around her as a young person in this world. She loves to play with colors, differents gradiants and textures.

Fire Walk With Me

"I'm the self inflicted, mind detonator, yeah
I'm the one infected, twisted animator
I'm a firestarter, twisted firestarter"

Fishmonger

Poor fishmonger hates his job... Cries for every fish he has to gut...

Lullabies for the Static God

I had an idea of a coven of witch goblins that had to play some tunes to appease the Static God and lull him back into its slumber.

Guardian

Got inspired to create this when I saw a picture of a Nicobar pigeon for the first time...

# João Rafael
Heya!
My name is João Rafael and I am a Portuguese queer artist/graphic designer, operating freelance under the moniker Daus since 2015, and I am currently based in Leeds, UK.
I attended Soares dos Reis Art School in Portugal where I graduated with a specialization in Graphic Design and subsequently moved to Bournemouth, UK to attend Arts University Bournemouth where I was awarded a Ba Hons Diploma in Illustration.
I pride myself on my versatility and unusual approach to image-making, always experimenting with new techniques and transposing a sense of movement and hysteria to my artwork. Through the years I have developed a special interest in creating album artwork, posters, and experimenting with augmented reality.
I currently work at a bookshop to help pay for rent and bills, but I am hopeful that one day I will be able to provide for myself just with my art.

Morningstar

Done after completing Ratchet and Clank two times in a row. The crazy weapons in the original ps2 games always inspired me when I was a kid.

Chemical Warrior

Inspired by Hideo Kojima's creations.
Completely fell in love with Tretij Rebenok while playing MGSV, such a cool character. Weaponizing children is both an interesting and scary concept.
